; --- Misc ---
Update View=F5
Read Only Toggle=Alt+Z
Database Summary=Alt+D
Table Summary=Alt+T
Statistics Column=Control+Shift+S
Select Columns=Alt+S
Graphics Column=Control+Shift+G
Graphics Grid=Alt+Shift+G
Select Column=None
Extract Regex=Control+Shift+X
Append Cell=Alt+C
Copy Cell=Control+C
Copy Visible Cells=None
Copy Column=None
Copy Grid=None
Jump Next Initial=None
Query=Control+Q
Query History=Alt+Shift+Q
Test Database=None
Test Driver=None
Open Managed Copy=None, Open a SQLite database as a throwaway working copy: edits stay in the copy and the original is untouched until you Save Database
Describe Table=None, Per-column data profile of the current table: declared type and key/null/FK flags, plus live null and distinct counts with min and max values
Facet Column=None, List the distinct values in the column under the cursor with their row counts, then filter the grid to a chosen value
Open File Folder=Alt+Backslash
Command Prompt=Control+Slash, Open a Windows command prompt in the folder of the currently-open database
Enter Console=Control+GraveAccent
Sqlean Console=Control+Shift+GraveAccent
Invoke Script=Alt+V
Edit Script=Alt+Shift+V
Open Script Folder=None
Evaluate Expression=Control+Equals, Evaluate a one-off expression and hear the result
Edit Settings=Alt+Shift+E, or F12

